9:
I could read you like a book, you
know.
13:
Looks like your lackeys are finished.
Ready to give up yet?
22:
I admit, it's impressive that you can
unleash attacks so quickly. However,
your inability to hide your killing
intent betrays your inexperience.
24:
This fight is over. Take us to your
leader.
28: Do you really expect... Tohru to just—
51: Wait, Tohru, we just came to talk—
72:
W-we were just testing them, Tohru!
We needed to know if they would be
of use—
77:
A test? Hm. You're up for inspection
next.
82: I'll hear what you have to say. Come.
87:
...Nimbus, do you think you could
handle him if worse came to worst?
90:
If I got to move first? Sure. But in a
fair fight, I'm a goner.
95:
We've still got a chance to talk
before it comes to that. Let's do this.
104:
Sakuya Hoshino of the Starsayers
said she watched it come down with
the lightning a month ago.
108:
I don't know anything about a lance.
I only saw that bolt from the sky.
110:
Mishima, you know all of us got our
powers after witnessing the
Dragon's Iris.
115:
He's talking about something most
of us saw in a dream right before we
powered up.
118:
Why're you explaining it to them?
They have powers. They should've
seen it themselves.
123:
I'm afraid our abilities aren't the
same as yours.
126:
What? You expect me to believe you
were born with yours?
131:
We come from another world.
Things work differently there.
134:
Pffft, did you hit your head or
something? Or is this your idea of a
joke—
140:
So... You somehow crossed the Void
to get here?
143:
The Void? Are you talking about the
Rift?
146:
I'm not sure what you're getting at,
but I promise we're not from this city.
151:
Just look at Nimbus and I. Shouldn't
our appearances be proof enough?
156:
It's impossible... You couldn't have
gotten here in one piece...
161:
Whatever the truth, I'm willing to
work with you.
167:
Let me make one thing clear—we're
not going to help you loot and steal.
170:
What, are you telling me you'd
rather take the cult's side?
174:
You're the one attacking them.
Sakuya said she was willing to lend
you guys a hand if you'd lay down
your arms.
178:
I know you don't believe that
garbage.
182:
She'll give the lip service you want,
then throw you to the dogs.
185:
If you start dancing to her tune, then
you're done for.
189:
...You're right. We don't trust her. But
neither do we have a reason to trust
you.
192: Then go visit the Shibuya River.
195:
It flows underneath the station. You
can decide who to trust once you
see what's there.
198:
We use force to get our way, but
they use lies. You'll have to pick your
poison.
204:
I don't get it... Why do YOU have to
go do those things?
208:
I'm sorry... I know you don't want me
to leave, but I promise I'll come back.
211:
Stella, it'll be a while before you and
Nova finish forging a connection to
Starview, right?
216:
Yes. Even once we're ready, we can
only take a small number of people
at a time... and the connection will
only hold so long.
219:
Like I thought... We won't be able to
save everyone that way.
224:
We are forcibly creating a gate
there, after all. But we'll have more
options once you manage to
retrieve the Antipode Lance.
228:
Basically, your main goal hasn't
changed—find Leve and take back
the lance. Good luck, partner.
241:
I'm afraid I agree with Nao in this
situation. Why must you be the one
to put yourself in such danger?
244:
Surely someone else will find a
solution—
248:
Not everyone is fine with standing
on the sidelines and saving their
own behind, Mr. Takamori. But you
wouldn't know that, would you?
258:
You're right that it doesn't have to be
me.
262: But if I can do something, I will.
265: I'm sorry, but that's just who I am.
